WEBVTT

00:01.084 --> 00:04.046
[ Dog barking, train whistle
blowing in distance ]

00:15.015 --> 00:17.184
[ Police radio chatter ]

00:22.022 --> 00:23.941
[ Engine revs ]

00:23.941 --> 00:26.568
[ Siren chirps ]

00:26.568 --> 00:29.905
[ Car doors open, close ]

00:29.905 --> 00:33.867
I have so many questions,
I don't know where to start.

00:33.867 --> 00:36.870
So I'll open with...

00:36.870 --> 00:38.539
"Where you headed?"
To the bar on the corner.

00:38.539 --> 00:41.124
I'm taking my brother
for one last drink.

00:41.124 --> 00:43.293
I'm sorry for your loss.
As am I.

00:43.293 --> 00:45.254
But y-you can't just
be transporting a --

00:45.254 --> 00:47.214
There is a body in there?
Yes, sir.

00:47.214 --> 00:49.508
My brother Kenny.

00:49.508 --> 00:52.386
Uh, who knows the next time
I'll see him, if ever.

00:52.386 --> 00:54.805
If you know what I mean.
Yeah. No, actually,

00:54.805 --> 00:56.765
I don't know
what you're talking --

00:56.765 --> 00:58.475
I'm sorry. Could you
open the lid for us, please?

00:58.475 --> 00:59.893
Yeah.

00:59.893 --> 01:01.478
Oh.
We there yet?

01:02.688 --> 01:04.273
Your brother's not dead.
No, sir.

01:04.273 --> 01:05.941
So why is he
in a coffin?

01:05.941 --> 01:08.610
Oh, we just found it on the side
of the road a ways back.

01:08.610 --> 01:10.070
Pretty cool, right?
Celina: Okay, but you said

01:10.070 --> 01:12.114
it was the last drink
and you'll never see him again.

01:12.114 --> 01:13.865
Yeah, well, he's moving
to the Valley tomorrow,

01:13.865 --> 01:15.158
so who knows?
I just...

01:15.158 --> 01:17.119
It's right
behind my eyes.

01:17.119 --> 01:20.789
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh, oh,
oh, oh, oh, oh ♪
It's like a hot knife.

01:20.789 --> 01:25.627
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

01:25.627 --> 01:27.713
[ Indistinct conversations,
camera shutter clicking ]

01:27.713 --> 01:29.715
Alright, so,
what do we have?

01:29.715 --> 01:32.509
Ji-hoon Kim --
49, liquor-store owner.

01:32.509 --> 01:34.094
Two gunshots to the head.

01:34.094 --> 01:36.096
Also has a fractured jaw
and bloodied ear.

01:36.096 --> 01:37.931
There were
broken bottles inside.

01:37.931 --> 01:39.433
He fought off a robber?

01:39.433 --> 01:41.977
Or tried to. Looks like
he tried to make a run for it.

01:41.977 --> 01:43.645
Anyone see anything?

01:43.645 --> 01:46.440
Hey, Detectives. A C.I. of mine
says Double R did it

01:46.440 --> 01:48.400
because our victim
wouldn't pay up.

01:48.400 --> 01:50.986
Double R?
Some new girl gang.

01:50.986 --> 01:53.572
I'm sorry, did he just act like
girls aren't dangerous?

01:53.572 --> 01:55.949
Yes, he did. In front of two
of the most dangerous women who

01:55.949 --> 01:58.118
have ever walked this earth.
Who could have you assigned

01:58.118 --> 02:00.203
to traffic control
on the surface of the sun.

02:00.203 --> 02:01.913
Man: <i>Officer Jan,</i>
<i>we need you inside.</i>

02:01.913 --> 02:04.249
Uh, yeah, Copy that.
I'm on my way.

02:04.249 --> 02:06.126
Oh, yeah. Yeah.
You better run.

02:06.126 --> 02:07.627
[ Chuckles ]

02:07.627 --> 02:10.714
♪♪

02:10.714 --> 02:12.049
Good morn--

02:12.049 --> 02:13.759
[ Whispering ]
Oh. Good morning.

02:13.759 --> 02:15.969
Sorry. Ignore me.

02:15.969 --> 02:18.055
Please continue.
We need to talk.

02:18.055 --> 02:20.682
That's never a good start
to a conversation.

02:20.682 --> 02:22.601
So, I've been speaking
with Celina.

02:22.601 --> 02:24.144
Oh! I just discovered
a worse one.

02:24.144 --> 02:26.438
The energy in your house
is off.

02:26.438 --> 02:28.231
<i>Our</i> house.
That's really sweet,

02:28.231 --> 02:29.483
but not the point.

02:29.483 --> 02:31.318
Okay. I'm excited to hear
what the point is.

02:31.318 --> 02:33.320
Ever since the engagement,
whenever I'm here,

02:33.320 --> 02:36.198
I feel off center,
if that makes any sense.

02:36.198 --> 02:37.908
But I couldn't
put my finger on it.

02:37.908 --> 02:40.035
But after talking to Celina,
we realized

02:40.035 --> 02:41.953
that the wallpaper color
in the bedroom

02:41.953 --> 02:43.789
doesn't line up
with your astrological sign

02:43.789 --> 02:45.040
and the couch fabric

02:45.040 --> 02:47.668
is completely counter
to your birth element.

02:48.710 --> 02:51.713
Okay, see, the plan was
for you to rub off on Celina,

02:51.713 --> 02:53.006
not the other way around.

02:53.006 --> 02:55.300
What about the blocked energy?
Oh, don't you worry.

02:55.300 --> 02:58.095
I'll talk to Celina today
all about that blocked energy.

02:58.095 --> 03:00.180
Bye! [ Smooches ]
Love you.

03:00.180 --> 03:02.683
Okay. That's it.
Be safe out there.

03:02.683 --> 03:04.309
But before you leave,
one more thing,

03:04.309 --> 03:06.019
what you've all
been waiting for.

03:06.019 --> 03:07.479
So, I'll make this quick.

03:07.479 --> 03:09.981
Pay raises from
the last union negotiation

03:09.981 --> 03:11.191
have gone into effect.

03:11.191 --> 03:12.526
-Yeah.
-Yay.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.610
[ Applause ]

03:13.610 --> 03:15.862
♪♪

03:15.862 --> 03:18.323
Check your pay stubs,
and we'll see what --

03:18.323 --> 03:20.492
You're interrupting a briefing.
Are you Sergeant Wade Grey?

03:20.492 --> 03:23.120
No.
That'd be me.

03:23.120 --> 03:25.789
You've been served.

03:25.789 --> 03:29.418
"Elijah Stone vs.
The City of Los Angeles, LAPD,

03:29.418 --> 03:32.462
Wade Grey, Wesley Evers,
and Angela Lopez."

03:32.462 --> 03:38.009
♪♪

03:38.009 --> 03:40.095
A civil suit
and a Pitchess motion.

03:40.095 --> 03:42.556
Alright.
Briefing's over.

03:42.556 --> 03:44.307
♪♪

03:44.307 --> 03:45.725
Celina:
What's a Pitchess motion?

03:45.725 --> 03:48.061
It's a request to see
a cop's personnel file.

03:48.061 --> 03:50.647
Everything -- IA complaints,
even the bogus ones.

03:50.647 --> 03:53.775
It's a great way
to, uh, block energy.

03:53.775 --> 03:56.236
Why don't you go set up the
shop. I'll meet you out there.

03:56.236 --> 03:58.405
Lopez: Hey, union rep.
Anything you can do to help?

03:58.405 --> 03:59.781
Not much I can do
about the lawsuit.

03:59.781 --> 04:01.491
As far as
the Pitchess motion goes,

04:01.491 --> 04:03.618
I can call the City Attorney's
office right now

04:03.618 --> 04:05.328
and make sure they're
following POBR on that.

04:05.328 --> 04:06.455
Thanks.

04:06.455 --> 04:07.956
I've been hit with
20 Pitchess motions

04:07.956 --> 04:09.624
and never had a judge
grant one.

04:09.624 --> 04:10.709
Yeah, but if it <i>is</i> granted,

04:10.709 --> 04:12.377
Elijah can use it
to support his claims

04:12.377 --> 04:14.588
of "violation
of civil rights,

04:14.588 --> 04:16.840
false arrest by a peace officer
with a warrant,

04:16.840 --> 04:18.925
racial profiling,
civil conspiracy."

04:18.925 --> 04:20.469
This is unbelievable.

04:20.469 --> 04:21.845
I mean, the guy is
a major drug trafficker.

04:21.845 --> 04:23.263
If he thinks he can sue

04:23.263 --> 04:25.348
a defense attorney
turned prosecutor and win,

04:25.348 --> 04:27.601
he doesn't know how badass
my husband is in the courtroom.

04:27.601 --> 04:29.394
Damn straight.
Uh, you want to take a minute,

04:29.394 --> 04:31.354
or should we ask
about Chen?

04:33.857 --> 04:36.109
What about Chen?

04:36.109 --> 04:37.736
We caught a D. B.
this morning,

04:37.736 --> 04:40.322
a shopkeeper who refused
to pay protection money

04:40.322 --> 04:42.157
to a street gang
called Double R.

04:42.157 --> 04:43.742
Rowena Razors
out of Rowena Gardens?

04:43.742 --> 04:45.535
Gang task force
doesn't have much on them

04:45.535 --> 04:47.704
except their leader,
Shana Quelli.

04:47.704 --> 04:49.664
She was released from Valley
State Prison three months ago.

04:49.664 --> 04:52.083
She's been extorting
store owners on her turf.

04:52.083 --> 04:53.293
Harper:
Our victim took a stand,

04:53.293 --> 04:55.837
and the Razors made
an example out of him.

04:55.837 --> 04:57.756
Harper and Lopez need you

04:57.756 --> 04:59.090
to infiltrate the gang

04:59.090 --> 05:01.510
to get some evidence,
murder weapon.

05:01.510 --> 05:03.178
A confession
would be best.

05:03.178 --> 05:05.722
Uh...they're not going
to let me anywhere near them.

05:05.722 --> 05:07.766
You're U. C. now, right?

05:07.766 --> 05:09.726
Gaining access and building
trust is the name of the game.

05:09.726 --> 05:13.313
♪♪

05:13.313 --> 05:14.606
You got it.

05:14.606 --> 05:16.149
I'll figure it out.

05:18.068 --> 05:19.569
[ Car doors close ]

05:19.569 --> 05:20.987
Tim: Hello, ma'am.
We had a noise complaint.

05:20.987 --> 05:22.447
Yelling.
Everything okay?

05:22.447 --> 05:24.449
I was just arguing
with my son.

05:24.449 --> 05:25.742
Ain't no need
for the police.

05:25.742 --> 05:28.286
Okay, so what's
the problem, ma'am?

05:28.286 --> 05:29.329
My son, Tabin.
Mm-hmm.

05:29.329 --> 05:30.789
He won't listen.

05:30.789 --> 05:33.416
He cuts school.
He won't pick up after himself.

05:33.416 --> 05:35.085
And the mouth
on that boy.

05:35.085 --> 05:37.003
And how old's your son?
15.

05:37.003 --> 05:38.630
He threaten you?
He knows he better not!

05:38.630 --> 05:41.758
Okay. Any drugs, weapons,
other criminal behavior?

05:41.758 --> 05:43.677
Tabin?
Absolutely not.

05:43.677 --> 05:45.053
I see him drifting.

05:45.053 --> 05:47.389
He's running the streets
instead of doing schoolwork.

05:47.389 --> 05:50.183
Told him he's gonna
end up like his sister.

05:50.183 --> 05:52.310
I already lost one child.

05:52.310 --> 05:53.728
I'm not gonna lose another.

05:53.728 --> 05:55.313
And let me guess -- He didn't
want to hear that, huh?

05:55.313 --> 05:56.898
He says I don't know
what I'm talking about.

05:56.898 --> 05:59.150
Starts yelling
and -- and slamming doors.

05:59.150 --> 06:01.444
I told him,
"You break my house,

06:01.444 --> 06:03.738
I'mma break your head."

06:03.738 --> 06:06.491
Okay. Well, we can't arrest him
if he hasn't committed a crime.

06:06.491 --> 06:08.493
Ain't nobody asking you
to do all that.

06:08.493 --> 06:11.496
You can't talk to him,
put the fear of Jesus in him,

06:11.496 --> 06:12.956
help keep him
out of trouble?

06:12.956 --> 06:14.583
I pay your salaries.

06:14.583 --> 06:18.086
You know what?
We <i>should</i> defund y'all ass.

06:18.086 --> 06:20.130
Look, um, I-I'll talk
to him, okay?

06:20.130 --> 06:21.214
Is he inside?

06:21.214 --> 06:22.465
Mm-hmm.

06:22.465 --> 06:23.592
[ Police radio chatter ]

06:32.350 --> 06:34.477
She did <i>not</i>
call the cops on me.

06:34.477 --> 06:35.937
Ma!
Hey, hold on.

06:35.937 --> 06:37.772
It's -- It's alright.

06:37.772 --> 06:38.899
Tabin, right?

06:38.899 --> 06:40.442
Officer Thorsen.
Call me Aaron.

06:40.442 --> 06:42.360
She's crazy, okay?

06:42.360 --> 06:44.946
Your mom didn't call us, okay?
But she is worried about you.

06:44.946 --> 06:47.449
What am I supposed to do?
Stay cooped up in here?

06:47.449 --> 06:48.825
I-I want
to live my life.

06:48.825 --> 06:50.243
Right,
and she wants you

06:50.243 --> 06:52.829
to live a long and good life,
too. All moms do.

06:52.829 --> 06:55.040
You know, it's just, sometimes,
they can trip about everything.

06:55.040 --> 06:56.291
Listen.
I know how you feel, okay?

06:56.291 --> 06:58.835
My mom,
she's a piece of work, too.

06:58.835 --> 07:01.921
Sometimes I feel like
she's the kid and I'm the adult.

07:01.921 --> 07:03.590
Yeah. Yeah. You know.

07:03.590 --> 07:05.884
Right. But you still got to
show her respect, okay?

07:05.884 --> 07:07.594
No matter how angry you get.

07:07.594 --> 07:09.179
When I was your age,
I was angry, too.

07:09.179 --> 07:12.098
Listen to her, right?
If you get upset or whatever,

07:12.098 --> 07:13.975
just take a beat
before answering.

07:13.975 --> 07:16.019
I mean, she changed
your diapers, man, okay?

07:16.019 --> 07:17.145
You owe her that.

07:19.439 --> 07:21.566
I hear you.
Anything else bothering you?

07:21.566 --> 07:23.151
Kids at school?
Nah.

07:23.151 --> 07:24.819
You use?
No, sir.

07:24.819 --> 07:26.738
Good. Any gangs
pressuring you to join?

07:28.031 --> 07:29.407
No, no.

07:29.407 --> 07:31.201
Here's my card, alright?

07:31.201 --> 07:33.411
It's got my cell on it.

07:33.411 --> 07:35.580
Anything stresses you out,
you give me a call, okay?

07:35.580 --> 07:37.791
But no more slamming
these doors. You feel me?

07:37.791 --> 07:38.833
Yes, sir.

07:38.833 --> 07:40.126
Alright.

07:42.462 --> 07:45.840
Yeah, as their union rep,
I just wanted to touch base.

07:45.840 --> 07:48.510
Thank you very much
for your time.

07:48.510 --> 07:49.928
What'd they say
about the Pitchess motion?

07:49.928 --> 07:52.430
That Lopez's
and Wesley's marriage

07:52.430 --> 07:54.265
is going to
complicate things.

07:54.265 --> 07:56.309
Elijah's gonna try
to prove prejudice.

07:56.309 --> 07:57.727
He may actually
have a case.

07:57.727 --> 07:58.895
Yeah, that's not good.

07:58.895 --> 08:00.647
No, that's not good at all.

08:00.647 --> 08:04.317
Uh, now, what was
Bailey talking to you about,

08:04.317 --> 08:06.444
uh, our house's energy
being blocked?

08:06.444 --> 08:08.113
Okay, look,
she came to me for advice.

08:08.113 --> 08:09.364
And you suggested
redecorating?

08:09.364 --> 08:11.324
[ Chuckles ] Okay, look,
it's more than that.

08:11.324 --> 08:13.201
It's about having
your home's energy line up

08:13.201 --> 08:14.786
as you build
a home together.

08:14.786 --> 08:16.913
It's that couch.
She hates the couch.

08:16.913 --> 08:19.207
Definitely the couch. It's like
a positive-energy black hole.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.250
I'd start there.

08:20.250 --> 08:21.209
"Start"?

08:24.212 --> 08:25.296
Barista: Enjoy.
Have a great day.

08:25.296 --> 08:26.214
Thank you.

08:26.214 --> 08:27.924
Double latte,
cranberry scone?

08:27.924 --> 08:30.260
[ Sighs ]
You know me well.

08:30.260 --> 08:33.263
Damn.
He's taking the last one?

08:33.263 --> 08:35.265
♪ <i>And if you real about it</i> ♪

08:35.265 --> 08:36.516
Hello, Wesley.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.184
Elijah.
What, you following me?

08:38.184 --> 08:40.061
Well, I heard you come here
every morning.

08:40.061 --> 08:42.147
Well, the best scone
in town.

08:42.147 --> 08:43.982
You know, I never
would have guessed

08:43.982 --> 08:46.901
from your sad, little office
or that beater that you drive

08:46.901 --> 08:48.153
that you're
old-money rich.

08:49.821 --> 08:52.115
What's it like
having generational wealth?

08:52.115 --> 08:54.034
I don't care about money.

08:54.034 --> 08:56.161
I care about justice,
the rule of law.

08:56.161 --> 08:58.079
Spoken like someone
with a ton of money.

08:58.079 --> 08:59.497
Hmm.
Well, don't worry.

08:59.497 --> 09:01.624
I'll be relieving you
of your burden.

09:01.624 --> 09:04.169
♪ <i>Get in, get in</i> ♪

09:04.169 --> 09:07.005
It's been nice,
but you need to leave.

09:07.005 --> 09:09.299
Your lawsuit's malicious.

09:09.299 --> 09:10.759
I'm not leaving.
This is my spot.

09:10.759 --> 09:13.344
Well, not anymore.

09:13.344 --> 09:15.847
Given the fact that you
planted evidence on me,

09:15.847 --> 09:17.599
are married
to a police detective,

09:17.599 --> 09:20.268
and have the full force
of the D. A.'s office behind you,

09:20.268 --> 09:22.729
it's easy to see
how you kept your job.

09:22.729 --> 09:25.398
My only choice was to file
a restraining order against you.

09:25.398 --> 09:26.649
The judge granted it.

09:26.649 --> 09:28.234
This gentleman here
just served you.

09:28.234 --> 09:30.987
I'mma be here every day,
which means you'd better not be.

09:30.987 --> 09:33.531
♪♪

09:33.531 --> 09:34.574
Wesley.

09:34.574 --> 09:39.662
♪♪

09:39.662 --> 09:42.290
Take the scone.
That's all you're gonna get.

09:42.290 --> 09:44.667
♪♪

09:44.667 --> 09:46.503
[ Wrapper crinkling ]

09:46.503 --> 09:50.673
♪♪

09:50.673 --> 09:52.509
[ Cellphone chimes ]

09:52.509 --> 09:55.553
It's that kid Tabin.
[ Police radio chatter ]

09:55.553 --> 09:57.597
"Took a beat
like you said.

09:57.597 --> 10:00.016
Now Mom has me
grocery shopping.

10:00.016 --> 10:02.393
Thanks a lot."
Smile emoji.

10:02.393 --> 10:05.271
[ Cellphone clicking ]
"What time's dinner?"

10:05.271 --> 10:06.981
I think that kid's
gonna be alright.

10:06.981 --> 10:09.400
Be careful.
Puppies are a lot of work.

10:09.400 --> 10:11.027
[ Mid-tempo music plays ]

10:11.027 --> 10:12.779
What?

10:12.779 --> 10:13.905
You just got a puppy.

10:13.905 --> 10:14.948
Meaning I'm
blurring the lines?

10:14.948 --> 10:17.534
Meaning protect
your personal space.

10:17.534 --> 10:20.411
Lucy got a puppy over a year
ago. Now she's living with her.

10:20.411 --> 10:22.163
I mean, as long
as his mom's a good cook.

10:22.163 --> 10:25.041
♪♪

10:25.041 --> 10:27.001
Lucy: Oh, hey. I ran
a record management search

10:27.001 --> 10:28.503
on the Rowena Razors.

10:28.503 --> 10:31.005
Here is everything
from the gang task force.

10:31.005 --> 10:33.466
They are playing catch-up.

10:33.466 --> 10:35.385
I --
This doesn't make sense.

10:35.385 --> 10:38.304
I mean, criminal history,
arrest reports.

10:38.304 --> 10:39.556
These girls
are heavy hitters.

10:39.556 --> 10:41.599
They've all done time
for meth trafficking,

10:41.599 --> 10:43.643
attempted murder,
manslaughter.

10:43.643 --> 10:45.854
Why is the current intel
so light?

10:45.854 --> 10:47.272
Well, you said it.
Girls.

10:47.272 --> 10:49.190
Everyone dismisses
female gangs

10:49.190 --> 10:51.484
as some sort
of throwback curiosity,

10:51.484 --> 10:54.237
like the Pink Ladies.

10:54.237 --> 10:55.572
And if they do
take them seriously,

10:55.572 --> 10:58.575
they are written off
as drug mules or prostitutes,

10:58.575 --> 11:00.285
not the ones who are actually
calling the shots.

11:00.285 --> 11:01.995
This is what
I was trying to say earlier.

11:01.995 --> 11:03.246
It's gonna be
tough to get in.

11:03.246 --> 11:04.497
They'll be a tight-knit group,
you know?

11:04.497 --> 11:07.250
Suspicious of outsiders.
Yeah. No doubt.

11:07.250 --> 11:09.043
But don't make the same mistake
that men do

11:09.043 --> 11:11.921
and write them off
as just little girls.

11:11.921 --> 11:13.506
They're a real threat.

11:13.506 --> 11:14.507
Well, so am I.

11:14.507 --> 11:15.508
♪♪

11:15.508 --> 11:17.385
[ Chuckles ]

11:17.385 --> 11:20.930
Remember, those stop signs
are there for a reason.

11:20.930 --> 11:22.140
Drive safe.

11:22.140 --> 11:23.391
[ Police radio chatter ]

11:23.391 --> 11:26.019
[ Sighs ] You know,
here's what's concerning me.

11:26.019 --> 11:27.437
About what?
Bailey.

11:27.437 --> 11:30.982
She's feeling off-center
ever since she proposed.

11:30.982 --> 11:32.859
It's not you.
It's the energy in your house.

11:32.859 --> 11:34.444
Let's just say,

11:34.444 --> 11:35.904
for the sake of argument,
it's not about the couch.

11:35.904 --> 11:37.363
Mm-hmm.
I just don't like

11:37.363 --> 11:38.698
that she doesn't feel
comfortable in our home.

11:38.698 --> 11:40.283
Gun!

11:40.283 --> 11:41.618
Police! Drop the gun!

11:41.618 --> 11:43.411
7-Adam-15.
Shots fired at our location.

11:43.411 --> 11:45.705
I need assistance.
Check on the victim.

11:45.705 --> 11:52.879
♪♪

11:52.879 --> 11:54.547
[ Dog barking ]

11:54.547 --> 12:04.515
♪♪

12:04.515 --> 12:08.686
[ Dog whining ]

12:08.686 --> 12:11.022
♪♪

12:11.022 --> 12:13.316
Good boy.

12:13.316 --> 12:14.901
Police.
I know you're in there.

12:14.901 --> 12:15.652
Throw the gun out.

12:15.652 --> 12:19.155
♪♪

12:19.155 --> 12:20.531
Now step out nice and slow.

12:20.531 --> 12:21.824
Keep your hands
where I can see them.

12:21.824 --> 12:24.577
[ Hinges creak ]

12:24.577 --> 12:25.995
Turn around.

12:25.995 --> 12:27.914
Hands on your head.
Step towards me.

12:27.914 --> 12:29.082
Right there.

12:29.082 --> 12:31.542
[ Handcuffs click ]
Alright.

12:31.542 --> 12:33.086
Nice dog.

12:33.086 --> 12:35.004
Code 4.
Suspect in custody.

12:35.004 --> 12:36.297
[ Tires screech ]

12:38.299 --> 12:39.884
[ Police radio chatter ]

12:39.884 --> 12:41.678
He got what he deserved.

12:41.678 --> 12:44.931
I'm sure you feel that way,
but no one deserves that.

12:44.931 --> 12:46.307
He's dead.
[ Sighs ]

12:46.307 --> 12:48.017
Yeah, well,
bullets will do that.

12:48.017 --> 12:50.019
No, I mean, like,
he's a corpse.

12:50.019 --> 12:51.312
Skin's cold and pale.

12:51.312 --> 12:52.939
The vessels in his eyes
are trucking.

12:52.939 --> 12:54.816
I mean, I'd say he's been dead
for at least an hour

12:54.816 --> 12:56.067
before she shot him.

12:56.067 --> 12:58.778
Why would she shoot someone

12:58.778 --> 13:00.280
who's already dead?
[ Siren approaching ]

13:03.324 --> 13:05.785
Nolan:
You'll see that little trailer

13:05.785 --> 13:06.577
halfway down on the left.
That's where I found her hiding.

13:06.577 --> 13:07.996
Hello, sir.

13:07.996 --> 13:11.040
Our victim is Alvin Mitchelssen.
He's an M. D.

13:11.040 --> 13:13.793
He was working at a urgent care
center in Woodland Hills.

13:13.793 --> 13:16.045
This his residence?
Yes, sir.

13:16.045 --> 13:17.547
Any family?
Uh, he's got a wife

13:17.547 --> 13:19.215
we're trying to get ahold of.
She hasn't picked up yet.

13:19.215 --> 13:20.717
I had realized
there was no blood

13:20.717 --> 13:22.510
coming out of the bullet holes,
which was weird.

13:22.510 --> 13:24.637
But then I saw blood pooling
on the seat,

13:24.637 --> 13:26.889
and that's when I realized
he was already dead.

13:26.889 --> 13:29.392
The M.E. found a stab wound
on his lower back.

13:29.392 --> 13:31.060
They figure that's
the likely cause of death.

13:31.060 --> 13:32.937
There was no blood
leading to the car.

13:32.937 --> 13:35.773
So we figure he was stabbed
as he was entering the vehicle,

13:35.773 --> 13:37.692
but he was losing blood
so quickly,

13:37.692 --> 13:40.403
he passed out before he was able
to drive himself to a hospital.

13:40.403 --> 13:42.071
Um...

13:42.071 --> 13:43.364
Good work,
both of you.

13:43.364 --> 13:45.158
[ Scoffs ] This guy must have
been a piece of work

13:45.158 --> 13:47.452
for two people to set out
to kill him on the same day.

13:47.452 --> 13:49.412
Uh, sir, would you mind

13:49.412 --> 13:51.914
if Juarez and I continued
working this case?

13:51.914 --> 13:54.125
I know you have your hands full
with the Elijah Stone stuff.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.626
[ Sighs ]
I appreciate that.

13:55.626 --> 13:57.045
Okay.
You two work this.

13:57.045 --> 13:58.713
Just keep me in the loop
with any developments.

13:58.713 --> 14:00.548
Yes, sir.
Head back.
Talk to the shooter.

14:00.548 --> 14:02.341
If we can figure out
why she wanted him dead,

14:02.341 --> 14:03.509
maybe we can
determine why

14:03.509 --> 14:04.969
someone else would
want him dead, too.

14:04.969 --> 14:07.096
Got it. Um...

14:07.096 --> 14:08.306
What am I
charging her with?

14:09.682 --> 14:12.060
Um, desecration
of a human corpse?

14:12.060 --> 14:14.395
Right. But if she didn't know
it was a corpse...

14:14.395 --> 14:15.646
Then it'd be
attempted murder.

14:15.646 --> 14:16.981
But --
But without a victim...

14:16.981 --> 14:18.566
Alright.
Give me a second.

14:18.566 --> 14:20.026
Bradford,
we have a suspect

14:20.026 --> 14:23.112
who fired into an already
expired individual.

14:23.112 --> 14:25.364
Tim: <i>Ooh, that's a tough one.</i>
<i>Could be murder one,</i>

14:25.364 --> 14:27.116
<i>but maybe just</i>
<i>discharging a firearm.</i>

14:27.116 --> 14:28.701
<i>They either get a trial</i>
<i>or a ticket.</i>

14:28.701 --> 14:30.244
Thanks for nothing.
Nolan: Uh, you know what?

14:30.244 --> 14:32.246
I'll just call the D. A.'s office
when I get back.

14:32.246 --> 14:34.457
I'm sure they've done this
a hundred times.

14:34.457 --> 14:36.501
May--

14:36.501 --> 14:38.503
Probably not a hundred.
That doesn't seem very...

14:38.503 --> 14:40.129
Yeah.

14:40.129 --> 14:43.216
I could pose as a store owner,
get them for extortion.

14:43.216 --> 14:46.052
No. We need them for the murder.
Keep looking.

14:46.052 --> 14:48.638
[ Indistinct conversations ]

14:48.638 --> 14:50.014
Oh.

14:50.014 --> 14:52.725
What is it?
One of the Razors,

14:52.725 --> 14:54.435
Vina Cordon --

14:54.435 --> 14:56.562
there was a 4-15 called
at her house today,

14:56.562 --> 14:58.481
and Tim and Aaron took it.

15:01.359 --> 15:03.361
Hey, you guys caught a 4-15
this morning?

15:03.361 --> 15:04.904
Yeah. It was cute.

15:04.904 --> 15:06.364
Cute?
All puppies are cute.

15:06.364 --> 15:09.117
[ Scoffs ] Until they borrow
your earrings and they lose one.

15:09.117 --> 15:11.661
Yeah, the mom asked us
to talk to her 15-year-old son.

15:11.661 --> 15:12.954
He's a good kid.

15:12.954 --> 15:15.206
Aaron's protégé has been
texting him nonstop.

15:15.206 --> 15:17.333
"Who should I take to prom?
What's good on Hulu?"

15:17.333 --> 15:19.085
Did the mom
mention a daughter?

15:19.085 --> 15:20.628
Yeah,
she said she lost one.

15:20.628 --> 15:22.213
Didn't want her son
to end up the same way,

15:22.213 --> 15:23.881
and I thought she meant,
like, O. D. or something.

15:23.881 --> 15:25.508
No.
Uh, Vina Cordon.

15:25.508 --> 15:27.093
She runs with
the Rowena Razors.

15:27.093 --> 15:29.345
R-2.
We want to put Lucy under,

15:29.345 --> 15:31.639
but we can't find an in.
Your kid might be our ticket.

15:31.639 --> 15:34.475
If your puppy vouches for her,
it can go a long way.

15:34.475 --> 15:37.603
I don't know. Having a kid act
as a C.I. on his own sister?

15:37.603 --> 15:39.105
I mean, they might not
even be in touch.

15:39.105 --> 15:40.815
She doesn't have
any violent priors,

15:40.815 --> 15:43.151
but we like the gang leader
for doing our shop owner.

15:43.151 --> 15:45.111
Okay, so you're not
going after the sister.

15:45.111 --> 15:46.821
The kid's a minor. We're gonna
need the mom's permission.

15:46.821 --> 15:48.364
No,
I-I'm not feeling that.

15:48.364 --> 15:50.283
Why would we put him
in this situation?

15:50.283 --> 15:52.118
I get it.
But it's one intro.

15:52.118 --> 15:53.411
It's not like
it's a buy or anything.

15:53.411 --> 15:55.913
Yeah,
but it opens the door.

15:55.913 --> 15:58.082
Isn't there another way?
There really isn't.

15:58.082 --> 16:00.251
Alright, look, how about we keep
an eye on the kid ourselves,

16:00.251 --> 16:02.461
make sure he's safe?

16:02.461 --> 16:03.754
If we don't do this,

16:03.754 --> 16:05.965
we risk letting a suspect
get away with murder.

16:05.965 --> 16:09.177
♪♪

16:09.177 --> 16:10.720
Understood.

16:10.720 --> 16:12.305
Sure.
Whatever you need.

16:12.305 --> 16:15.099
Great.
We'll set it up.

16:15.099 --> 16:18.644
Well, do you want to tell us
why you shot Alvin Mitchelssen?

16:18.644 --> 16:20.229
A few years ago,

16:20.229 --> 16:23.524
my dad
hurt his back at work.

16:23.524 --> 16:28.362
And Dr. Mitchelssen
gave him opioids for the pain.

16:28.362 --> 16:29.697
And he just kept...

16:29.697 --> 16:32.783
upping the dosage.

16:32.783 --> 16:36.287
And I went and I told him,
"My dad is abusing the pills.

16:36.287 --> 16:37.705
He needs help."

16:37.705 --> 16:39.874
And Dr. Mitchelssen
just ignored me.

16:43.127 --> 16:47.048
[ Voice breaking ]
My dad O. D.'d three months ago,

16:47.048 --> 16:49.050
and he would
still be around today

16:49.050 --> 16:50.968
if it wasn't
for that monster.

16:50.968 --> 16:52.929
Well, did you report him
to the medical board?

16:52.929 --> 16:55.723
I did everything
that you were supposed to do,

16:55.723 --> 16:57.725
and no one cared.

16:57.725 --> 16:59.602
I wasn't gonna just
let him kill my father.

16:59.602 --> 17:00.895
He had to pay.

17:00.895 --> 17:03.314
And that is why
I killed him.

17:03.314 --> 17:05.775
And I am ready for whatever
consequences that may bring.

17:05.775 --> 17:07.568
[ Breathes shakily ]

17:07.568 --> 17:09.403
Well, Abby, I've got
some good news for you,

17:09.403 --> 17:12.198
and I've got
some good news for you.

17:12.198 --> 17:15.451
Dr. Mitchelssen was already dead
when you shot him this morning.

17:15.451 --> 17:16.827
[ Gasps ]

17:16.827 --> 17:18.955
Uh, I don't understand.
[ Sighs ]

17:18.955 --> 17:21.499
So I'm -- I'm not being
arrested for murder?

17:21.499 --> 17:24.627
No. We will be charging you
with vandalism,

17:24.627 --> 17:27.922
discharging a firearm in public,
and mutilation of a corpse.

17:27.922 --> 17:31.509
So I'm not gonna be spending
the rest of my life in prison?

17:31.509 --> 17:34.971
No. After we process you,
you'll be free to go,

17:34.971 --> 17:36.973
and someone will explain to you
how you can get your gun back.

17:36.973 --> 17:40.017
Keep it.
[ Sniffles ]

17:40.017 --> 17:41.269
Having it in the house
in the first place

17:41.269 --> 17:43.229
is what got me here.

17:43.229 --> 17:45.940
[ Laughing, crying ]

17:45.940 --> 17:47.733
Look, it's a big decision.
You know, we don't usually

17:47.733 --> 17:50.111
involve minors,
but it's the only way.

17:50.111 --> 17:52.238
I knew this Shana girl
was nasty.

17:52.238 --> 17:54.365
I told Vina,
"Stay away from her."

17:54.365 --> 17:57.285
Is it dangerous?
It's just an introduction.

17:57.285 --> 18:00.288
One meeting. But we'll be set up
on surveillance.

18:00.288 --> 18:01.789
You'll be there?
Yes, ma'am.

18:01.789 --> 18:04.750
And what do you think?
Is this a good idea?

18:04.750 --> 18:06.877
I think it's our best bet
to get Shana off of the streets.

18:06.877 --> 18:08.588
That's not what I asked.

18:08.588 --> 18:10.298
Do you think
he should do it?

18:10.298 --> 18:13.175
[ Inhales deeply ]

18:13.175 --> 18:14.176
Yes.

18:14.176 --> 18:17.138
♪♪

18:17.138 --> 18:19.974
If we can get Vina
away from Shana, then...

18:19.974 --> 18:21.684
maybe she'll
come back home.

18:21.684 --> 18:23.060
I hope so, baby.

18:25.021 --> 18:26.731
Alright.
I'll do it.

18:26.731 --> 18:27.940
Do I get a gun?

18:27.940 --> 18:29.233
No.

18:29.233 --> 18:31.110
Do I at least
get to wear a wire?

18:31.110 --> 18:32.153
No.

18:32.153 --> 18:34.071
You guys are
real cops, right?

18:34.071 --> 18:36.949
♪♪

18:36.949 --> 18:38.534
[ Door opens ]

18:38.534 --> 18:41.329
Thank you for coming in.
We just had a few questions.

18:41.329 --> 18:42.371
Would you like to sit?

18:42.371 --> 18:43.581
Yeah.

18:45.750 --> 18:48.669
First, uh, may I say
how sorry we are

18:48.669 --> 18:50.004
for the loss
of your husband.

18:50.004 --> 18:52.548
Oh. Thank you.

18:52.548 --> 18:53.716
I-I'm still in shock.

18:53.716 --> 18:56.010
I can only imagine.

18:56.010 --> 18:57.887
When was the last time
you spoke with Alvin?

18:57.887 --> 18:59.388
This morning.

18:59.388 --> 19:01.390
I had a conference
downtown,

19:01.390 --> 19:04.310
so I left before him,
which is unusual.

19:04.310 --> 19:06.062
He's usually
out the door first.

19:06.062 --> 19:09.440
Can you think of anyone who
would want to harm your husband?

19:09.440 --> 19:11.233
I don't understand.

19:11.233 --> 19:13.444
What do you mean,
harm my husband?

19:13.444 --> 19:15.988
W-Well,
he was stabbed.

19:15.988 --> 19:17.365
Right before
he was shot.

19:17.365 --> 19:19.575
Somebody stabbed him,
then shot him?

19:19.575 --> 19:20.993
Two people, we think.

19:20.993 --> 19:22.453
At the same time?
No.

19:22.453 --> 19:24.163
So two different people
killed my husband?

19:24.163 --> 19:25.706
No, technically,
just one.

19:25.706 --> 19:27.541
None of this makes sense.
He's a doctor.

19:27.541 --> 19:30.461
He -- He dedicated his life
to helping people.

19:30.461 --> 19:32.672
I-I knew he had
heart problems.

19:32.672 --> 19:34.757
That's what I thought you were
gonna tell me killed him.

19:34.757 --> 19:37.343
I-I don't understand why
someone would want him dead.

19:37.343 --> 19:39.053
So there's nothing
you could think of

19:39.053 --> 19:40.680
that could lead to this?
I mean, no arguments

19:40.680 --> 19:42.807
with co-workers,
patients?

19:42.807 --> 19:45.142
All his patients
loved him.

19:45.142 --> 19:48.229
Well, thank you very much again
for coming in.

19:48.229 --> 19:50.398
And we are so sorry
for your loss.

19:50.398 --> 19:52.525
[ Door closes ]
Uh, Rich, would you show

19:52.525 --> 19:54.568
Mrs. Mitchelssen
back to the front desk?

19:54.568 --> 19:57.113
If we have any more questions,
we'll be in touch.

19:58.531 --> 20:01.409
Uh, please...

20:01.409 --> 20:03.411
find whoever did this
to my husband.

20:03.411 --> 20:04.745
Of course.

20:07.832 --> 20:09.417
[ Exhales deeply ]

20:09.417 --> 20:11.419
Sounds like she didn't really
know her husband.

20:11.419 --> 20:13.337
Or he's
a really good liar.

20:13.337 --> 20:15.172
♪♪

20:15.172 --> 20:16.757
♪ If you gon' do it,
do it right ♪

20:16.757 --> 20:18.968
♪ So if I hit it once,
I know I can do it twice ♪

20:18.968 --> 20:20.928
♪ Anything come up out my mouth,
I'mma back it up ♪

20:20.928 --> 20:21.929
♪ Don't judge me cuz ♪

20:21.929 --> 20:26.142
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

20:26.142 --> 20:28.352
Yeah, that's
the sister, Vina.

20:28.352 --> 20:29.603
Lopez: I have Shana,
the shooter.

20:29.603 --> 20:31.647
Tim:
Copy. Lucy, you're up.

20:31.647 --> 20:33.149
[ Engine revving ]

20:35.568 --> 20:36.777
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

20:36.777 --> 20:39.780
[ Engine revving ]

20:39.780 --> 20:41.949
Woman: Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
[ Tires screeching ]

20:41.949 --> 20:43.659
[ <i>Hip-hop music playing</i> ]

20:43.659 --> 20:44.952
[ Dog barking in distance ]

20:44.952 --> 20:48.080
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:48.080 --> 20:50.249
♪♪

20:50.249 --> 20:51.876
[ Scoffs ] Yo.

20:51.876 --> 20:53.711
You didn't invite me?

20:53.711 --> 20:56.088
Shana: What you want?

20:56.088 --> 20:57.548
You Vina?
Who are you?

20:57.548 --> 20:59.049
UPS.

20:59.049 --> 21:01.302
I got a special delivery
for you.

21:01.302 --> 21:03.262
♪♪

21:03.262 --> 21:04.513
What the hell you doing
with my brother?

21:04.513 --> 21:06.390
Get over there.

21:06.390 --> 21:10.686
♪♪

21:14.732 --> 21:17.735
♪♪

21:17.735 --> 21:19.570
Put that gun away.
Is that how you're
gonna thank me

21:19.570 --> 21:20.863
for saving your brother
from the cops?

21:20.863 --> 21:22.531
You a'ight?
Yeah.

21:22.531 --> 21:24.784
Man, you're wearing some
dumb genes in your family.

21:24.784 --> 21:26.535
Got some nerve
to be talking like that.
Okay.

21:26.535 --> 21:27.620
Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait.

21:27.620 --> 21:30.039
Look,
cops saw me boost a six.

21:30.039 --> 21:31.624
They chase you?
Two blocks.

21:31.624 --> 21:32.792
They would have
caught him

21:32.792 --> 21:34.794
if I didn't stop
and let him in my ride.

21:34.794 --> 21:37.046
That's the last time
I help a kid in need.

21:37.046 --> 21:41.759
♪♪

21:41.759 --> 21:44.303
Can't blame her...

21:44.303 --> 21:46.263
you rolling up
on a house like that.

21:46.263 --> 21:47.515
Could've been
a drive-by.

21:47.515 --> 21:50.392
Yeah. Well, I like
to make an entrance.

21:50.392 --> 21:51.644
And exit, too.

21:51.644 --> 21:52.978
[ Door closes ]

21:52.978 --> 21:54.563
Stay good,
little man.

21:54.563 --> 21:56.065
Peace.

21:56.065 --> 21:58.484
Yo, chica.

21:58.484 --> 21:59.652
Mm-hmm.
Chill.

21:59.652 --> 22:02.071
Grab a drink.

22:02.071 --> 22:03.489
Alright.

22:03.489 --> 22:06.700
♪♪

22:06.700 --> 22:08.369
Promise me
you're not gonna freak out.

22:08.369 --> 22:10.913
I never freak out.
I'm a very calm person.

22:10.913 --> 22:13.040
Don't even wo-- Whoa.

22:13.040 --> 22:14.625
This...

22:14.625 --> 22:16.836
This is so...much.

22:16.836 --> 22:19.213
Are we -- Are you -- Are we
redecorating the entire house?

22:19.213 --> 22:20.798
You said you weren't gonna
freak out.

22:20.798 --> 22:23.801
Listen, there are just
some samples I wanted
to look at together.

22:23.801 --> 22:27.721
Okay, can we just talk about why
you're not comfortable at home?

22:27.721 --> 22:30.349
I mean, this morning, you said
you've been feeling off-center.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.601
I think we should try
to figure out why.

22:32.601 --> 22:34.770
I want you to be happy
everywhere.

22:34.770 --> 22:36.355
I am.
Not entirely, though.

22:36.355 --> 22:39.191
You know this has nothing
to do with you. I'm just weird.

22:39.191 --> 22:41.235
Okay, well, maybe it doesn't
have anything to do with me,

22:41.235 --> 22:44.363
and maybe it has something to do
with the house after all.

22:44.363 --> 22:46.615
What do you mean?

22:46.615 --> 22:49.410
There's nothing of yours there.
It's all my stuff.

22:49.410 --> 22:51.620
Today we'll go get
some of your things,

22:51.620 --> 22:54.498
bring it over to the house,
and then it'll be <i>our</i> place.

22:54.498 --> 22:55.791
Thank you.

22:55.791 --> 22:57.418
Oh, come on. I'm sorry
I didn't think of it sooner.

22:57.418 --> 23:00.212
You know, there <i>is</i>
this one lounge chair

23:00.212 --> 23:01.672
that I love
and I've been missing.

23:01.672 --> 23:03.674
And every time you sit in it,
it feels like it's hugging you.

23:03.674 --> 23:05.301
See? A hugging chair.

23:05.301 --> 23:06.802
That sounds like
a wonderful addition.

23:06.802 --> 23:08.387
[ Door opens ]
Oh, hey. Hey, girl.

23:08.387 --> 23:09.513
How you doing?
Hi.

23:09.513 --> 23:10.472
Yeah.
Oh, this is nice.

23:10.472 --> 23:11.974
Ooh.

23:13.434 --> 23:15.311
A-An investigation
had been launched

23:15.311 --> 23:16.854
by the Medical Board
of California.

23:16.854 --> 23:18.814
Dr. Mitchelssen was
racking up complaints,

23:18.814 --> 23:21.692
mainly about
over-prescribing opioids.

23:21.692 --> 23:24.153
He had all of his scripts filled
at just one pharmacy,

23:24.153 --> 23:26.363
deep in the Valley.
That's not suspicious at all.

23:26.363 --> 23:27.740
Mm-hmm.
Alright. Back to business.

23:27.740 --> 23:30.576
Um, unless you two
want to handle the pharmacy,

23:30.576 --> 23:31.619
and I'll get the chair?

23:31.619 --> 23:33.913
[ Laughing ]
No, no. Go, go, go.

23:33.913 --> 23:35.247
Don't worry
about the chair.

23:35.247 --> 23:38.042
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

23:38.042 --> 23:38.959
[ Cellphone clicks ]

23:38.959 --> 23:41.253
What's up?
I got news.

23:41.253 --> 23:43.047
Elijah's
Pitchess motion failed.

23:43.047 --> 23:44.131
<i>He won't be able</i>
<i>to get his hands</i>

23:44.131 --> 23:46.717
on all the B. S. IA complaints
in your file.

23:46.717 --> 23:48.886
But?
But he decided
to file his own.

23:48.886 --> 23:51.680
Against me?
On what grounds?

23:51.680 --> 23:54.934
He claims you kicked him in
the nuts and slapped him around,

23:54.934 --> 23:56.518
pulled his hair,
body-slammed him.

23:56.518 --> 23:59.188
Never happened, although now
I'm regretting my restraint.

23:59.188 --> 24:01.649
I know. Hey, it's his word
against yours.

24:01.649 --> 24:03.150
He won't win.

24:03.150 --> 24:04.818
We thought he'd spent
a lifetime in prison.

24:04.818 --> 24:06.278
Now he's walking free.

24:06.278 --> 24:07.655
Don't underestimate him.

24:07.655 --> 24:08.864
[ Cellphone clicks ]

24:08.864 --> 24:11.450
Listen, don't let Elijah Stone
get to you.

24:11.450 --> 24:12.660
You got this.

24:12.660 --> 24:15.496
[ <i>Hip-hop music playing</i> ]

24:15.496 --> 24:16.956
You know, we keep it cool
like that. You want a beer?

24:16.956 --> 24:19.375
Yeah.

24:19.375 --> 24:21.877
♪ <i>Money be da mission,</i>
<i>city slickin'</i> ♪

24:21.877 --> 24:22.878
♪ <i>Back to back whips,</i>
<i>no penny pinchin'</i> ♪

24:22.878 --> 24:24.171
Appreciate it.

24:24.171 --> 24:25.339
You from L. A.?

24:25.339 --> 24:26.590
Phoenix.

24:26.590 --> 24:28.300
My cellie at Valley State
lives here,

24:28.300 --> 24:29.760
so I'm crashing
on her couch.

24:29.760 --> 24:31.929
You were at Valley?

24:31.929 --> 24:33.639
10 months.

24:33.639 --> 24:35.599
I did 24.

24:35.599 --> 24:38.185
Who's your cellie?

24:38.185 --> 24:40.229
Shawty Ross.

24:40.229 --> 24:41.397
I know Shawty.

24:41.397 --> 24:43.399
<i>You were cellies?</i>

24:43.399 --> 24:44.900
Hm.

24:48.278 --> 24:50.864
That says something.

24:50.864 --> 24:52.825
Tell her I said what up.

24:52.825 --> 24:54.118
For sure.

24:54.118 --> 24:55.828
Shawty's a C.I.
on D. O. J.'s payroll.

24:55.828 --> 24:57.496
She'll confirm
Lucy's cover.

24:57.496 --> 24:59.832
Okay. Good.
We should pull Tabin out now.

24:59.832 --> 25:01.667
No, he's fine.

25:01.667 --> 25:03.919
Sir, no, it's not.
You are endangering this kid

25:03.919 --> 25:05.462
all because it's good
for Lucy's career.

25:05.462 --> 25:07.506
Excuse me?

25:07.506 --> 25:10.092
Lucy: <i>...time,</i>
<i>walk out a free woman.</i>

25:10.092 --> 25:12.553
I'm sorry.
Shana: <i>Ain't no surprise.</i>
<i>Shawty don't play.</i>

25:12.553 --> 25:14.596
I shouldn't have said anything.
Vina: <i>No, she don't.</i>

25:14.596 --> 25:17.933
So, what game you guys run?
Cars? Vike, goodfella, monkey?

25:17.933 --> 25:19.810
What's the deal?
Drugs bring
too much attention.

25:19.810 --> 25:21.478
Tabin: Yo, what'd you say
about my sister?
We stick to the shadows.

25:21.478 --> 25:23.397
Yeah, let's just say
we in the security business.

25:23.397 --> 25:25.691
[ Indistinct shouting ]

25:25.691 --> 25:26.608
♪♪

25:26.608 --> 25:27.985
Hey!

25:27.985 --> 25:30.154
[ Indistinct shouting ]

25:30.154 --> 25:32.906
♪♪

25:32.906 --> 25:35.200
Oh, yeah.
You see it, huh?

25:35.200 --> 25:37.244
You see it?

25:37.244 --> 25:40.664
♪♪

25:40.664 --> 25:42.666
Put that away.

25:42.666 --> 25:45.377
[ Crowd murmuring indistinctly ]

25:46.962 --> 25:48.338
Are you good?
Yeah, I'm good.

25:48.338 --> 25:50.174
Good?
You just got your ass beat.

25:50.174 --> 25:52.301
Hell yeah,
he got his ass whupped.

25:52.301 --> 25:53.969
Hey, look, take this.
Settle up with him later.

25:53.969 --> 25:54.762
Come on.

25:54.762 --> 25:59.975
♪♪

25:59.975 --> 26:01.727
Nah. I'm -- I'm good.

26:01.727 --> 26:06.106
♪♪

26:06.106 --> 26:08.275
Boy can't even
hold a gun.

26:08.275 --> 26:10.360
Scared of a gun!
[ Scoffs ]
[ Laughs ]

26:10.360 --> 26:11.737
"Nah. I'm good."

26:11.737 --> 26:13.072
[ Both laugh ]

26:13.072 --> 26:16.241
♪♪

26:16.241 --> 26:18.285
Alright. She's in.
Let's peel off.
[ Engine starts ]

26:18.285 --> 26:19.953
Roger.

26:19.953 --> 26:21.538
[ Seat belt clicks ]

26:21.538 --> 26:30.714
♪♪

26:30.714 --> 26:40.057
♪♪

26:40.057 --> 26:41.266
Come on.

26:41.266 --> 26:47.689
♪♪

26:47.689 --> 26:54.071
♪♪

26:57.533 --> 27:00.244
Aaron: Look, it may feel like
a big deal now,

27:00.244 --> 27:01.662
but things like this always blow
over, okay? People will forget.

27:01.662 --> 27:03.080
You're just saying that.

27:03.080 --> 27:04.873
Nah, it's true, man. You know
how many times I been beat up?

27:04.873 --> 27:06.041
Is that why you're so ugly?

27:06.041 --> 27:07.668
Wow. Okay.
Althea: Get off me!

27:07.668 --> 27:10.212
Get away from me!
Don't touch me!

27:10.212 --> 27:12.464
Woman: Ma'am!
Where's my son?! Where --

27:12.464 --> 27:14.967
[ Sighs ] I knew I shouldn't
have allowed this.

27:14.967 --> 27:16.385
You said
it wasn't dangerous.

27:16.385 --> 27:18.137
It was just a little dust-up
with another teen.

27:18.137 --> 27:21.014
You call this a dust-up?
Well, I call it a screw-up.

27:21.014 --> 27:23.267
And what about Vina?
You put her in danger, too?

27:23.267 --> 27:24.643
Maybe I should tell her
what's going on.

27:24.643 --> 27:26.186
Ma'am,
you can't do that.

27:26.186 --> 27:28.230
You expose that we have
an officer undercover,

27:28.230 --> 27:30.774
it'll jeopardize their life
and your son's.

27:30.774 --> 27:33.861
He's right. As soon as
Tabin made his introduction,

27:33.861 --> 27:35.320
I should have pulled him out
immediately.

27:35.320 --> 27:37.906
My son's done
playing cops and robbers.

27:37.906 --> 27:40.242
You hear?
Yes, ma'am.

27:40.242 --> 27:41.493
Come on, baby.

27:41.493 --> 27:48.542
♪♪

27:48.542 --> 27:51.211
With all those prescriptions
Dr. Mitchelssen was writing,

27:51.211 --> 27:53.171
I mean, you'd think
this pharmacy would
be a little busier.

27:53.171 --> 27:54.381
[ Police radio chatter ]

27:54.381 --> 28:00.762
♪♪

28:00.762 --> 28:02.055
[ Van door closes ]

28:02.055 --> 28:03.682
[ Siren wails in distance ]

28:03.682 --> 28:08.687
♪♪

28:08.687 --> 28:13.984
♪♪

28:13.984 --> 28:15.819
Well, that's why
they don't look busy.

28:15.819 --> 28:17.237
They're shipping in bulk.

28:17.237 --> 28:20.532
♪♪

28:20.532 --> 28:22.159
[ Engine starts ]

28:22.159 --> 28:31.460
♪♪

28:31.460 --> 28:33.670
[ Siren chirping ]

28:33.670 --> 28:37.674
♪♪

28:38.717 --> 28:40.928
[ Car doors close ]

28:42.971 --> 28:44.389
Nolan: License
and registration, please.

28:44.389 --> 28:46.099
Uh, did I do
something wrong, Officer?

28:46.099 --> 28:47.100
We'll get to that.

28:47.100 --> 28:47.976
Alright.

28:51.396 --> 28:52.773
You mind telling me
what's in the van?

28:52.773 --> 28:55.442
Just, uh, making
some deliveries.

28:55.442 --> 28:56.735
Show me.

29:05.953 --> 29:07.037
Ta-da!
[ Chuckles ]

29:07.037 --> 29:08.580
Just some boxes.

29:08.580 --> 29:09.331
[ Van door closes ]
Why don't we open them up

29:09.331 --> 29:10.415
and take a look?
Uh...

29:10.415 --> 29:12.334
I don't think
I have to do that.

29:12.334 --> 29:13.585
Do I?

29:13.585 --> 29:15.796
Normally...no.

29:15.796 --> 29:17.631
You wouldn't have to show me
what's in the boxes.

29:17.631 --> 29:20.801
But, the fact is, your pupils
are the size of pinholes,

29:20.801 --> 29:23.220
and you can't seem
to stop licking your lips,

29:23.220 --> 29:25.889
which makes me believe you're
driving under the influence.

29:25.889 --> 29:28.600
<i>Now</i> I can see
what's in the boxes.

29:28.600 --> 29:30.060
The law is so confusing.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

29:30.060 --> 29:31.269
Not if you
don't break it.

29:31.269 --> 29:32.396
Step back.

29:38.110 --> 29:39.945
Did you know it's illegal
to possess prescription drugs

29:39.945 --> 29:41.571
assigned to anyone else?

29:41.571 --> 29:43.740
"Janet Wilson."
I'm guessing that's not you.

29:43.740 --> 29:44.908
That's my nana.
Mm.

29:44.908 --> 29:46.493
I'm her caregiver.

29:46.493 --> 29:48.787
Mm.

29:48.787 --> 29:50.372
"Thomas Jeffries."

29:50.372 --> 29:53.208
Poor Thomas.
He's having such a tough time.

29:53.208 --> 29:54.793
[ Chuckles ]
Hands behind your back.

29:54.793 --> 29:56.670
[ Handcuffs clicking ]

29:56.670 --> 29:59.256
What do you know about
Alvin Mitchelssen?

29:59.256 --> 30:01.383
Never heard of him.
Dr. Alvin Mitchelssen?

30:01.383 --> 30:04.011
Look, we've got a dead doctor
writing prescriptions

30:04.011 --> 30:05.762
getting filled
out at that pharmacy.

30:05.762 --> 30:08.724
And here you are, picking up
those very same scripts.

30:08.724 --> 30:10.767
Whoa. Hold on.
You're not hanging that on me.

30:10.767 --> 30:12.394
Then who are
we hanging it on?
Uh --

30:12.394 --> 30:15.272
Look, I noticed
the ink on your hand.

30:15.272 --> 30:18.400
Rolling Seventies?
That's a tough group of guys.

30:18.400 --> 30:19.985
I'm guessing they're gonna
sell these pills on the street.

30:19.985 --> 30:21.403
You're just a middleman.

30:21.403 --> 30:23.363
Tell me this, though.
Any of those guys

30:23.363 --> 30:25.282
willing to do your time for you
if they were here?

30:25.282 --> 30:27.534
Mnh-mnh.

30:27.534 --> 30:29.327
Come on, man.
Just tell us who's in charge,

30:29.327 --> 30:30.579
and we'll keep your name
out of it.

30:30.579 --> 30:33.540
[ Sighs ]

30:33.540 --> 30:35.959
♪♪

30:35.959 --> 30:38.462
Callis Caputo, okay?
He did the doctor.

30:38.462 --> 30:39.963
Where do we find
this Callis?

30:39.963 --> 30:42.215
This is a good party.

30:42.215 --> 30:43.967
Except for my brother
getting his ass whupped.

30:43.967 --> 30:45.510
Yo, my moms
got him so whipped,

30:45.510 --> 30:47.179
he ain't ever gonna make it
on these streets.

30:47.179 --> 30:48.346
I mean,
ain't that a good thing?

30:48.346 --> 30:50.766
Maybe he'll get to live
a regular life.

30:50.766 --> 30:52.350
Doing what?
Whatever he wants.

30:57.147 --> 30:58.690
Yeah, what you know?

30:58.690 --> 30:59.983
Don't disrespect me.

30:59.983 --> 31:01.526
Shana: She ain't.

31:01.526 --> 31:03.653
Sit down.

31:03.653 --> 31:05.405
I told you,
you got to chill.

31:05.405 --> 31:07.074
'Specially after you know.

31:07.074 --> 31:08.992
What happened?
You nosy, you know that?

31:08.992 --> 31:10.660
Step off.
[ Laughs ]

31:10.660 --> 31:11.953
That's Shawty's girl.

31:11.953 --> 31:14.498
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:14.498 --> 31:16.750
We got to make a run.
Want to come?

31:16.750 --> 31:18.585
Yeah.
Soon as I finish this.

31:18.585 --> 31:20.837
[ Indistinct conversations ]

31:24.883 --> 31:26.885
[ <i>Man singing in Spanish</i> ]

31:26.885 --> 31:28.720
[ Door bells jingle ]

31:28.720 --> 31:30.180
I already paid you.

31:31.681 --> 31:33.183
[ Clatter ]

31:33.183 --> 31:34.810
We're gonna be by
twice a week now.

31:34.810 --> 31:35.769
[ Women speaking
indistinctly ]

31:35.769 --> 31:37.270
I-I can't pay that.

31:37.270 --> 31:40.398
That's what the liquor store
owner said. You heard about him?

31:40.398 --> 31:41.858
"I can't pay."

31:41.858 --> 31:44.569
Even when I put a gun to
his head. He left me no choice.

31:44.569 --> 31:46.571
[ Breathing shakily ]

31:46.571 --> 31:48.115
Okay.

31:48.115 --> 31:49.449
I'll pay you
whatever you want.

31:49.449 --> 31:51.827
You know what?
Hey, man.

31:51.827 --> 31:52.953
He said he could pay.

31:52.953 --> 31:54.621
Don't interrupt me
when I'm doing business.

31:54.621 --> 31:56.832
I already told you.
Do not disrespect me.

31:56.832 --> 31:58.542
Stop.

31:58.542 --> 32:00.252
The liquor store was enough.

32:00.252 --> 32:02.045
We don't need more blood.

32:02.045 --> 32:03.380
And I told you
to get rid of that.

32:03.380 --> 32:04.673
It's my lucky piece.

32:04.673 --> 32:05.841
Get rid of it.

32:05.841 --> 32:06.800
[ Clicks tongue ]

32:09.010 --> 32:10.929
See you in a few days.

32:10.929 --> 32:13.306
[ <i>Man singing continues</i> ]

32:13.306 --> 32:14.474
[ Door opens ]

32:14.474 --> 32:20.147
♪♪

32:26.153 --> 32:28.446
The City Attorney's offering
to pay you a settlement.

32:28.446 --> 32:30.532
You should take it.

32:30.532 --> 32:32.617
You know,
I lost everything

32:32.617 --> 32:35.412
when I decided to help
you get your wife
back from La Fiera.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.748
You turned me
into a pariah.

32:38.748 --> 32:40.584
Now I have to start
from the bottom.

32:40.584 --> 32:42.085
But it's all good.

32:42.085 --> 32:44.171
I will win, and the damages
will be paid out

32:44.171 --> 32:45.922
from everyone's
personal accounts.

32:45.922 --> 32:50.218
Now, that may not hurt you,
Richie Rich.

32:50.218 --> 32:54.181
But it most certainly will hurt
Nolan and Harper and Grey.

32:54.181 --> 32:58.393
Where they gonna find a half
a million dollars each, huh?

32:58.393 --> 33:01.897
I'll keep coming, adding more of
your little friends to my suit.

33:01.897 --> 33:03.481
I'll take everything
away from you

33:03.481 --> 33:06.693
until you say sorry for
taking everything away from me.

33:06.693 --> 33:08.778
You want me to apologize?
To <i>you?</i>

33:10.322 --> 33:11.615
Something along
these lines.

33:12.782 --> 33:14.701
In public.

33:14.701 --> 33:18.246
♪♪

33:18.246 --> 33:20.916
And, Counselor,
make me believe it.

33:20.916 --> 33:26.213
♪♪

33:26.213 --> 33:28.048
Sir, we I. D.'d a suspect
for our homicide.

33:28.048 --> 33:29.382
His name is Callis Caputo.

33:29.382 --> 33:31.176
He's a member of
the Rolling Seventies.

33:31.176 --> 33:33.178
Yeah, he's holed up at his shop,
surrounded by his crew.

33:33.178 --> 33:35.555
We need to be smart with how
we go about bringing him in.

33:35.555 --> 33:36.806
This could get ugly.

33:36.806 --> 33:38.725
They've been itching
to start trouble for weeks now.

33:38.725 --> 33:40.393
I don't want
to put a match to it.

33:40.393 --> 33:42.646
Well, then, sir,
I think I have an idea.

33:42.646 --> 33:46.691
♪♪

33:46.691 --> 33:48.777
[ Line ringing ]

33:48.777 --> 33:51.238
[ Cellphone ringing ]

33:51.238 --> 33:52.906
Yeah?
You need to run.

33:52.906 --> 33:54.241
The cops
are coming for you.

33:54.241 --> 33:55.909
How do you know?
They picked me up earlier.

33:55.909 --> 33:58.203
This is my one phone call, and
I'm using it to warn your ass.

33:58.203 --> 34:00.580
Run!
[ Siren chirping ]

34:00.580 --> 34:02.165
They're here already.

34:02.165 --> 34:03.667
My car's parked
behind the repair shop,

34:03.667 --> 34:04.584
halfway down the block.

34:04.584 --> 34:05.669
Keys are in the wheel well.

34:05.669 --> 34:07.170
Go now.

34:07.170 --> 34:08.672
♪ Hit the breakers,
yeah, we're gone ♪

34:08.672 --> 34:10.298
Stall the cops.

34:10.298 --> 34:12.467
♪ I only do it for the chase ♪

34:12.467 --> 34:15.637
♪ To see the look
on their face ♪

34:15.637 --> 34:18.723
♪ Big Electric ♪

34:18.723 --> 34:22.102
♪ Ultra Thesis ♪

34:22.102 --> 34:25.438
♪ Cut Express It ♪

34:25.438 --> 34:27.691
♪ Can you feel it? ♪

34:27.691 --> 34:29.234
Looking for these?
♪ Whoo ♪

34:29.234 --> 34:30.944
[ Siren chirping ]

34:30.944 --> 34:38.326
♪♪

34:38.326 --> 34:41.079
♪ Can you feel it? ♪

34:41.079 --> 34:42.747
Hands.
[ Handcuffs click ]

34:42.747 --> 34:45.375
Alright, come on.
Watch your head.
[ Cellphone rings ]

34:45.375 --> 34:46.793
Yeah, this is John Nolan.

34:48.336 --> 34:50.130
You're kidding me.

34:50.130 --> 34:53.466
Oh, my God.
You're not kidding me.

34:53.466 --> 34:55.343
No, I-I didn't
see that coming.

34:55.343 --> 34:57.387
Alright, thank you very much
for the call.

34:57.387 --> 35:00.181
What was that?
That was the coroner.

35:00.181 --> 35:02.726
The tox report came back
on Dr. Mitchelssen.

35:02.726 --> 35:04.603
It wasn't the shooting
that killed him,

35:04.603 --> 35:06.354
and it wasn't the stabbing,
either.

35:06.354 --> 35:08.815
Before all that,
he was poisoned.

35:08.815 --> 35:10.025
That's what
stopped his heart

35:10.025 --> 35:11.860
before he bled out
after being stabbed.

35:11.860 --> 35:14.571
Okay, so there's yet another
murderer out there?

35:14.571 --> 35:17.032
Yeah.
But not for long.

35:17.032 --> 35:18.158
Care for
a little overtime?

35:18.158 --> 35:27.292
♪♪

35:27.292 --> 35:28.293
Look who it is.

35:31.504 --> 35:34.299
[ Gearshift clicks ]

35:34.299 --> 35:36.176
What's up?
I just told Harper and Lopez

35:36.176 --> 35:37.594
that I've made Vina
as the shooter

35:37.594 --> 35:39.054
in the liquor store murder.

35:39.054 --> 35:40.764
Tabin's sister?
Not the gang leader?

35:40.764 --> 35:41.931
Vina: Look, I'm just
checking up on you

35:41.931 --> 35:43.516
after your little
ass-whuppin'.

35:43.516 --> 35:44.809
Man, I'm good. Fine.

35:44.809 --> 35:46.269
Alright.

35:46.269 --> 35:47.604
Look, I need you
to hold something for me.

35:47.604 --> 35:48.980
N-No. No.

35:48.980 --> 35:50.357
I'm sorry, Aaron.

35:50.357 --> 35:51.650
She practically admitted to
pulling the trigger.

35:51.650 --> 35:53.652
I'm pretty sure she's got
the murder weapon on her now.

35:53.652 --> 35:54.402
Come on.
No.

35:54.402 --> 35:56.196
Just hold it.

35:56.196 --> 35:57.447
Use it if you need to.

35:57.447 --> 36:02.327
♪♪

36:02.327 --> 36:04.120
Vina?
I don't want
to blow my cover.

36:04.120 --> 36:05.455
[ Engine starts ]
Tim: We got it.

36:05.455 --> 36:10.251
♪♪

36:10.251 --> 36:12.128
You know anything about this?
[ Tires screech ]

36:12.128 --> 36:14.005
Police!
Get on your knees now!

36:14.005 --> 36:15.173
What the hell?
Vina,
you're under arrest

36:15.173 --> 36:16.299
for the murder of
Ji-hoon Kim.

36:16.299 --> 36:17.550
What,
you called them?

36:17.550 --> 36:19.135
No, baby,
I swear I didn't!

36:19.135 --> 36:21.471
Get on your knees!
Alright! Alright.

36:21.471 --> 36:22.681
Gun!
Wait! No!

36:22.681 --> 36:25.350
♪♪

36:25.350 --> 36:26.601
Wait! What the hell
are you doing?!

36:26.601 --> 36:28.061
Tabin, what are you doing?
Drop the gun.

36:28.061 --> 36:29.020
No, no, no, no, no, no.
You brought this mess
to my house.

36:29.020 --> 36:30.105
Tabin,
give me the gun, man.

36:30.105 --> 36:31.189
Put it down!
You did this!

36:31.189 --> 36:32.607
Vina: No --
Vina, you did this.

36:32.607 --> 36:33.817
Tim: Drop the gun!
[ Muffled ]
Tabin, look at me.

36:33.817 --> 36:34.984
Althea: No!
Aaron: Give me the gun.

36:34.984 --> 36:36.903
Put it down!
Give me the gun, man.

36:36.903 --> 36:39.572
Give me the gun.
Give me the gun, Tabin, okay?

36:39.572 --> 36:41.408
Just give me the gun.

36:41.408 --> 36:44.744
Come on.
Give me the gun.

36:44.744 --> 36:49.874
♪♪

36:49.874 --> 36:51.668
You used me.

36:51.668 --> 36:54.379
♪♪

36:54.379 --> 36:56.131
Vina: What you mean?
Look, I'm sorry, okay?

36:56.131 --> 36:57.215
We just wanted you home.

36:57.215 --> 36:59.467
[ Handcuffs click ]

36:59.467 --> 37:02.053
♪♪

37:06.516 --> 37:09.144
[ Dog barking in distance ]

37:13.815 --> 37:14.858
[ Knock on door ]

37:17.527 --> 37:19.946
Officer Nolan.

37:19.946 --> 37:21.197
Did you find out
who killed my husband?

37:21.197 --> 37:22.991
We did.

37:22.991 --> 37:25.243
And we're
looking at her.

37:25.243 --> 37:26.619
What are you
talking about?

37:26.619 --> 37:27.912
It struck me as odd,

37:27.912 --> 37:31.124
but I couldn't quite
put my finger on why --

37:31.124 --> 37:33.585
why you acted so surprised

37:33.585 --> 37:35.754
when I told you your husband
was shot and stabbed,

37:35.754 --> 37:37.338
as if you expected
something else.

37:37.338 --> 37:39.674
Something like poisoning,
which would have presented to us

37:39.674 --> 37:41.509
as a heart attack,
like you assumed.

37:41.509 --> 37:43.720
And it would've worked,
had he not already been shot.
[ Scoffs ]

37:43.720 --> 37:45.138
And stabbed.
And stabbed.
Thank you.

37:45.138 --> 37:46.514
You're welcome.

37:46.514 --> 37:47.891
[ Chuckling ]
That's insane.

37:47.891 --> 37:50.101
We put a pharmacy
out of business today.

37:50.101 --> 37:52.312
They were filling
illegal scripts.

37:52.312 --> 37:54.063
They have you
on video surveillance

37:54.063 --> 37:55.482
using one of
Alvin's scripts

37:55.482 --> 37:57.650
to purchase the drugs you used
to stop his heart.

37:57.650 --> 38:00.153
[ Scoffs ]

38:00.153 --> 38:01.237
♪ You can feel it
in the moment ♪

38:01.237 --> 38:04.824
Did you know that he was
under investigation,

38:04.824 --> 38:08.161
about to go to prison for being
a complete and utter idiot?

38:08.161 --> 38:11.080
I thought I was at least owed
the life-insurance policy.

38:11.080 --> 38:14.042
Mrs. Mitchelssen,
you're under arrest for murder.

38:14.042 --> 38:15.418
Officer Juarez,
cuff her.

38:15.418 --> 38:16.419
♪ Like it was your last ♪

38:16.419 --> 38:18.296
♪ Live extra ordinary ♪

38:18.296 --> 38:19.130
[ Handcuffs click ]

38:19.130 --> 38:20.799
We matched Vina's gun.

38:20.799 --> 38:22.050
It was definitely
the murder weapon

38:22.050 --> 38:23.134
at the liquor store killing.

38:23.134 --> 38:25.345
So thanks for the help.

38:25.345 --> 38:26.763
Hey, how's your puppy?

38:26.763 --> 38:28.848
I reached out a couple of times
to see how he was doing.

38:28.848 --> 38:30.141
And? Did he respond?

38:30.141 --> 38:31.893
[ Clicks tongue ]

38:31.893 --> 38:34.562
Oh. Hey, you put a killer
in prison today.

38:34.562 --> 38:36.481
Yeah.

38:36.481 --> 38:38.066
It's his sister.

38:38.066 --> 38:39.776
He'll get it someday.

38:39.776 --> 38:41.069
♪ But you can't let up ♪

38:41.069 --> 38:42.237
I hope so.

38:42.237 --> 38:43.279
♪ No, you can't let go ♪

38:43.279 --> 38:44.614
Good night.

38:44.614 --> 38:45.532
Good night.

38:45.532 --> 38:46.574
♪ 'Cause you got that dream ♪

38:46.574 --> 38:47.784
♪ In your mind, oh ♪

38:47.784 --> 38:50.245
Hey, uh, I just wanted
to say I'm sorry

38:50.245 --> 38:52.288
for what I said
about Lucy.

38:52.288 --> 38:53.748
That was totally
out of line.

38:53.748 --> 38:55.792
It was.

38:55.792 --> 38:57.585
It's all good.

38:57.585 --> 38:58.878
Look, sometimes
tensions get high,

38:58.878 --> 38:59.879
but we get
the job done.

38:59.879 --> 39:01.506
You had my back,

39:01.506 --> 39:03.258
the way you threw yourself
in front of Mom for me.

39:03.258 --> 39:04.467
Oh, yeah,
she was gon' lay you out.

39:04.467 --> 39:05.510
Come on.

39:05.510 --> 39:07.178
♪♪

39:07.178 --> 39:08.638
♪ 'Cause you could
never really hold it ♪

39:08.638 --> 39:09.639
Wesley:
I don't have a choice.

39:09.639 --> 39:10.765
Lopez:
Let's fight him in court.

39:10.765 --> 39:12.600
You don't have
to do this.

39:12.600 --> 39:13.977
Yes, I do.

39:13.977 --> 39:15.770
[ Indistinct conversations ]

39:15.770 --> 39:17.355
[ Siren wails in distance ]

39:17.355 --> 39:19.315
From the heart,
Counselor.

39:19.315 --> 39:20.441
[ Clears throat ]

39:20.441 --> 39:22.443
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

39:22.443 --> 39:25.572
♪♪

39:25.572 --> 39:27.073
Thank you for coming.

39:27.073 --> 39:28.825
I'd like to apologize
to Elijah Stone

39:28.825 --> 39:32.120
for some of my conduct while
acting as his defense attorney.

39:32.120 --> 39:33.496
I made statements
to the LAPD

39:33.496 --> 39:35.832
which broke
attorney-client privilege,

39:35.832 --> 39:38.084
I misrepresented
the nature of his business,

39:38.084 --> 39:41.462
and I cooperated
in an LAPD investigation

39:41.462 --> 39:43.464
that involved wiretapping.

39:43.464 --> 39:46.259
My actions have been reported
to the state bar,

39:46.259 --> 39:48.511
and I have been
reprimanded.

39:48.511 --> 39:50.680
Mr. Stone's reputation
has been tarnished,

39:50.680 --> 39:52.348
and for that,
I am sorry.

39:52.348 --> 39:55.643
I'm relieved that
justice has been served.

39:55.643 --> 39:58.271
Mr. Stone deserves
a second chance...

40:00.148 --> 40:02.734
...and the full faith
of the community.

40:02.734 --> 40:05.904
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

40:05.904 --> 40:09.073
Thank you.
Thank you.

40:09.073 --> 40:12.952
I accept your apology,
Mr. Evers.

40:12.952 --> 40:16.164
I will also accept
an undisclosed settlement

40:16.164 --> 40:19.000
from the City of
Los Angeles.

40:19.000 --> 40:22.420
I'm glad to see
our elected officials working

40:22.420 --> 40:25.965
to right
this egregious wrong.

40:25.965 --> 40:27.884
I hope you all
have learned your lesson

40:27.884 --> 40:31.262
and will strive
to do better.

40:31.262 --> 40:32.764
Thank you.

40:32.764 --> 40:33.848
[ Camera shutters clicking ]

40:33.848 --> 40:35.516
[ Sighs ]

40:35.516 --> 40:42.774
♪♪

40:42.774 --> 40:44.025
[ Camera shutters clicking,
reporters clamoring ]

40:44.025 --> 40:45.068
Smile.

40:45.068 --> 40:46.653
[ Clamoring continues ]

40:49.489 --> 40:52.992
♪♪

40:52.992 --> 40:54.160
What are you
smiling about?

40:54.160 --> 40:55.954
I did a thing.

40:55.954 --> 40:58.456
What kind of thing?

40:58.456 --> 40:59.582
Close your eyes.
I'll show you.

40:59.582 --> 41:01.668
Oh, no.
[ Chuckles ]

41:01.668 --> 41:03.002
Keep walking.

41:03.002 --> 41:04.963
You trust me, right?
[ Whimpers ]

41:04.963 --> 41:07.757
Walking, we're walking,
we're walking.

41:07.757 --> 41:09.676
And...
open your eyes.

41:09.676 --> 41:11.761
[ Gasps ]

41:11.761 --> 41:13.763
I know we said we'd go
this weekend together
and get your stuff.

41:13.763 --> 41:14.847
I thought
I'd surprise you.

41:14.847 --> 41:16.599
Oh, thank you.

41:16.599 --> 41:18.434
♪ <i>If I could wish upon a star</i> ♪

41:18.434 --> 41:20.436
Now let's put it
back in storage.

41:20.436 --> 41:23.064
Yeah. Whoa, what?
I got your big hug chair.

41:23.064 --> 41:25.066
I don't want that thing
hugging me.

41:25.066 --> 41:27.735
It's hideous.
Oh, it's not...

41:27.735 --> 41:28.778
<i>that</i> hideous.

41:28.778 --> 41:30.613
No, really, it is.

41:30.613 --> 41:32.323
Especially next
to all your furniture.

41:32.323 --> 41:34.242
You have
such good taste.

41:34.242 --> 41:36.411
Yeah, especially
in fiancées.

41:36.411 --> 41:39.580
Aww.
♪ <i>Over the hills and far away</i> ♪

41:39.580 --> 41:41.749
Well, it can go back.

41:41.749 --> 41:45.253
But this...has to stay.

41:45.253 --> 41:47.005
[ Inhales sharply ]
I made it.

41:47.005 --> 41:49.048
You don't say.

41:49.048 --> 41:50.341
[ Chuckles ]

41:50.341 --> 41:52.427
It spent an hour too long
in the kiln.

41:52.427 --> 41:54.053
No, no, it's perfect.
This is excellent.

41:54.053 --> 41:56.347
It'll live right here.
Aww.

41:56.347 --> 41:58.224
And he will
bring us luck.

41:58.224 --> 42:00.768
There.
Now it's <i>our</i> home.

42:00.768 --> 42:02.478
[ Earthquake rumbling ]

42:02.478 --> 42:03.896
[ Needle scratches,
music stops ]

42:03.896 --> 42:06.482
[ Gnome shatters ]

42:06.482 --> 42:10.445
I'm sure that doesn't
mean anything.

42:10.445 --> 42:12.071
Oh.

42:14.699 --> 42:15.491
But you never
"gnome."

42:20.413 --> 42:23.416
-- Captions by VITAC --

42:23.416 --> 42:31.382
♪♪

42:31.382 --> 42:39.432
♪♪

42:39.432 --> 42:47.190
♪♪
